S-mobile group assignment

Create representative column

## create new variable(s)
s_mobile <- mutate(s_mobile, representative = 0)
## create new variable(s)
s_mobile_rep <- mutate(s_mobile_rep, representative = 1)

Bind rows on both dataset

s_mobile_cmb <- combine_data(
  x = s_mobile, 
  y = s_mobile_rep, 
  add = c(
    "customer", "churn", "changer", "changem", "revenue", 
    "mou", "overage", "roam", "conference", "months", "uniqsubs", 
    "custcare", "retcalls", "dropvce", "eqpdays", "refurb", 
    "smartphone", "highcreditr", "mcycle", "car", "travel", 
    "region", "occupation"
  ), 
  type = "bind_rows"
)
register("s_mobile_cmb")

Create churn_yes variable

## create new variable(s)
s_mobile_cmb <- mutate(s_mobile_cmb, churn_yes = ifelse(churn == "yes", 1, 0))

Create cweight variable

## create new variable(s)
s_mobile_cmb <- mutate(s_mobile_cmb, cweight = ifelse(churn == "yes", 1L, 49L))

Recode training = -1 where null

s_mobile_cmb <- mutate(s_mobile_cmb,training = ifelse(is.na(training), -1, training))

representations churn mean - 0.02 -> 2%

result <- logistic(
